-- Caspian Pipeline Crude Exports Fall in May From Year Earlier
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-06-07T14:42:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/caspian-pipeline-crude-exports-fall-in-may-from-year-earlier.html
The Caspian Pipeline Consortium,
which operates the only crude export pipeline in Russia with
foreign shareholders, said oil shipments through its terminal at
Novorossiysk fell in May.  The terminal shipped 2.397 million metric tons, or 18.8
million barrels, compared with 2.508 million tons, or 19.7
million barrels, a year earlier, CPC said on its  website .  The CPC pipeline, whose biggest corporate shareholder is
Chevron Corp. with a 15 percent stake, runs from  Kazakhstan  to
the  Black Sea . Russia owns 31 percent while Kazakhstan owns
20.75 percent. Exxon Mobil Corp., OAO Lukoil and a joint venture
between OAO Rosneft and Royal Dutch Shell Plc are among other
shareholders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
